    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-19T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-19T07:00:00-05:00" n="1220"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1220">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Turkey/349: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-19T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >February 19, 1943—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 20—4:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>311. Embassy’s 226 February 4.<note n="57" xml:id="d1220fn57">See footnote 47,
                            <ref target="#pg_1152">p. 1152</ref>.</note> The Assistant General
                    Manager of the Eti Bank in charge of chrome matters states that Turkish
                    authorities have not yet issued export licenses to the Germans for more than 500
                    tons of chrome. So far as the Embassy is aware no chrome has as yet left Turkey
                    for Germany.</p>
                <p>He confirmed the information contained in the Embassy’s 233 February 5 by
                    apologetically explaining that the shipment in question had been started due to
                    a misunderstanding of instructions at the mine.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
